Gary,<br><br>
I read, with interest, your last posts.  I laughed a &quot;littlle.&quot;  I knew many of the &quot;same people&quot; you did -- just different names.  No combat veteran that I know of ever placed blame on anyone -- we all knew fear.<br><br>
I recall Charlie shooting at me one time and missing.  I immediately hit the ground (seems like it took me six years to reach the dirt) and all I could think of was that Charlie was going to shoot the pimple off my ass that I had been scratching for the last two days.  Funny what pops into your mind at times.  I was scared -- not sure whether I pissed on myself or not -- was trying to hard to grind myself into the dirt to remember.<br><br>
I remember other days where I didn't seem to have fear -- just hunger and thirst.  I'm sure you know what I'm saying.<br>
Some days you're on others your not -- never could figure out why -- maybe it was something in the C-rats.<br><br>
Paul<br><br>
I'm enjoying your insights to the site.  Always nice to have another army grunt on line.  That ought to get a rise out of ____.  Calling us grunts makes me feel like Tim Taylor, the Tool man.
<p><code>--   (Paul) </code><p>


